summer at stanford university high school and college summer programs skip to content search search home programs international basics need to know about us apply login international basics related links international basics english proficiency test requirements document requirements process to obtain an f 1 student visa arriving at stanford scholarship information home international international basics international students are welcome to apply to any of the programs at stanford summer session we appreciate the contributions our international students make to the summer community at stanford each year the summer session hosts approximately 300 students who hail from many countries around the world the following information will assist students with planning for their summer at stanford all international students non us citizens or non us permanent residents are required to have an f 1 student visa in order to enroll at stanford for the summer quarter the summer session office will monitor enrollment throughout the quarter to ensure compliance students should not plan on entering the country using a tourist visa b 1 b 2 or a wt wb waiver if the intention is to enroll in and take courses for credit students should contact the summer session office if they have additional questions about their visa status most international students already attending a us institution who are planning to return to that institution in the autumn will be able to participate in the summer session programs using their current visa before students apply select the stanford summer session program that's right for the student please ensure that the program is correct based on the student's age and grade level once students have selected the program go to the related links menu on the left side of this screen review the program overview and how to apply web pages prior to applying specific instructions for all international applicants is explained on these pages in detail important international students are expected to take their courses for academic credit all international students obtaining an i 20 certificate of eligibility for nonimmigrant f 1 student status sponsored by stanford are required to enroll in a minimum of 8 units students are strongly encouraged to apply as early as possible to avoid delays in processing their i 20 certificate of eligibility for nonimmigrant f 1 student status stanford university home map & directions help stanford university summer session terms of use copyright complaints powered by eresources
